The extension is for three months and to the tune of $984 million. Ramaphosa revealed this in a letter to the Speaker of the National Assembly. According to the Constitution, the President must inform Parliament whenever he authorises the deployment of members of the SANDF including the number of soldiers deployed, the reasons for the decision and the cost implications. Northern Mozambique has been buffeted by Islamic State-linked militants who have targeted towns and villages for the past four years. The wave of violence has claimed over 3 000 lives and displaced more than 800 000 people.  --SABC-- 